[32m+[m[32m# Vanilla Cards Architecture[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWelcome to the **Vanilla Cards** package for Nativa CMS. This architecture is built on pure Vanilla JS, strictly structured CSS using the **BEM methodology**, and optimized bundling via **Vite**.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mOur primary goal is maximum performance (0kb framework overhead) and maintainable UI components.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The Architecture & Flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe asset pipeline is split into two main layers: **Core** and **Page-Specific Modules**. We do not bundle everything into one massive `app.js` or `style.css`.[m[41m [m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. The Core Bundle (`core-app` & `core-css`)[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Core is the foundational layer of the design system. It is loaded globally on **every page**.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **What it contains:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Tokens:** CSS Variables for colors, spacing, typography (`unified.css`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Components:** BEM styles that are reused everywhere (`button.css`, `vanilla-card.css`, `navbar.css`, `footer.css`).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Infrastructure:** The `SectionLoader` JS class that automatically instantiates sections based on `data-section` attributes.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Why?** By keeping global utilities and foundational UI components in one bundle, the browser caches it once, and every subsequent page load feels instantaneous.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. Page-Specific Bundles (e.g., `home.ts`)[m
[32m+[m[32mEach individual page or logical use-case gets its own entry point folder (e.g., `src/frontend/home/`).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **What it contains:**[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Styles (`home.css`):** Layout overrides or extremely specific styles that only belong to this page (e.g., a specific background image for the home hero).[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Logic (`home.ts`):** Page-specific JavaScript, such as an initialization script or unique third-party library that only this page needs.[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Why?**[m[41m [m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Performance:** We prevent "Dead CSS/JS". If a user visits the `/contact` page, they shouldn't be forced to download the CSS or JS for the `/home` page animations.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Isolation:** It prevents CSS conflicts. Page specific styling cannot accidentally break global UI components.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - **Perfectly aligns with Nativa's `AssetHelper`:** Our PHP backend dynamically injects ONLY the CSS/JS required for the current controller view using `AssetHelper::entryCssTags('home')`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The Asset Pipeline (Vite + PHP)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWe use Vite strictly as an asset bundler for the PHP backend, mapping sources to hashed production files.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Source Code:** You write modular TS/CSS in `packages/vanilla-cards/src/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Vite Build (`pnpm run build`):** Vite processes, minifies, and adds cache-busting hashes to the filenames, outputting them into `dist/`.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Manifest Generation:** Vite generates a `vanilla-cards-manifest.json` file. It maps source files to their new hashed names (e.g., `src/app.ts` -> `core-app.DYSIM4Cj.js`).[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **PHP Integration (`AssetHelper`):** The Nativa CMS backend reads this manifest. When the backend asks for the `home` entry point, PHP dynamically prints the `<link>` and `<script>` tags for exactly those hashed files.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## BEM Methodology (Block, Element, Modifier)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWe strictly use BEM to keep our CSS flat and highly performant.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Block:** Standalone entity (`.card`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Element:** Part of a block (`.card__title`)[m
[32m+[m[32m- **Modifier:** Flag that changes appearance (`.card--featured`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Best Practice Rule:** Never nest selectors deeply. Instead of `.card .title`, always use `.card__title`. Combine BEM with design tokens (`var(--brand-gold)`).[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## SEO & Accessibility (Lighthouse Best Practices)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWhen writing HTML views that consume this architecture, always ensure you follow these standards to keep Lighthouse scores at 100/100:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **Meta Description:** Every page must include a `<meta name="description" content="...">` tag in the `<head>`.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Main Landmark:** All primary page content (between the `<nav>` and `<footer>`) must be wrapped in a `<main>` tag. This is crucial for screen readers and accessibility.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Valid `robots.txt`:** Ensure the `public/robots.txt` is present and valid so crawlers don't hit a 404.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Preconnects:** Include `<link rel="preconnect" href="/" />` (or to your CDN) to speed up initial network requests.[m
[32m+[m[32m5. **Preloads:** Our Vite build naturally supports `modulepreload` for JS and `preload` for critical CSS when injected via PHP's `AssetHelper::entryCssTags()`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## How to Add a New Page Flow[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mLet's say you are building an `/about` page.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. Create the Source Files[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mmkdir src/frontend/about[m
[32m+[m[32mtouch src/frontend/about/about.ts src/frontend/about/about.css[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**`about.ts`**[m
[32m+[m[32m```typescript[m
[32m+[m[32mimport './about.css';[m
[32m+[m[32mconsole.log('About page initialized!');[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. Register it in `vite.config.ts`[m
[32m+[m[32mUnder `rollupOptions.input`:[m
[32m+[m[32m```typescript[m
[32m+[m[32minput: {[m
[32m+[m[32m  'core-app': resolve(__dirname, 'src/app.ts'),[m
[32m+[m[32m  'core-css': resolve(__dirname, 'src/css.ts'),[m
[32m+[m[32m  'home': resolve(__dirname, 'src/frontend/home/home.ts'),[m
[32m+[m[32m  'about': resolve(__dirname, 'src/frontend/about/about.ts') // <-- NEW[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3. Build & Consume[m
[32m+[m[32mRun `pnpm run build`. The new entry will be generated and logged in the manifest.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn your PHP View (`about.php`):[m
[32m+[m[32m```php[m
[32m+[m[32m<?php[m
[32m+[m[32m// Loads global styles and functionality[m
[32m+[m[32mecho AssetHelper::entryCssTags('core-css', 'vanilla-cards');[m
[32m+[m[32m$coreJs = AssetHelper::js('core-app', 'vanilla-cards');[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m// Loads ONLY the about page specific styles and functionality[m
[32m+[m[32mecho AssetHelper::entryCssTags('about', 'vanilla-cards');[m
[32m+[m[32m$aboutJs = AssetHelper::js('about', 'vanilla-cards');[m
[32m+[m[32m?>[m
[32m+[m[32m<script type="module" src="<?= $coreJs ?>" defer></script>[m
[32m+[m[32m<script type="module" src="<?= $aboutJs ?>" defer></script>[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEnjoy building fast, reliable interfaces![m
[32m+[m
