[32m+[m[32m# Project Rules and Guidelines[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis document outlines the rules and guidelines for development in the Vanilla Cards project.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## General Principles[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use pnpm for package management.[m
[32m+[m[32m- All code should be written in English.[m
[32m+[m[32m- No frontend frameworks; use pure Vanilla JS and CSS.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Maintain a modular architecture.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## CSS Rules[m
[32m+[m[32m- Strictly follow BEM (Block Element Modifier) methodology.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use CSS custom properties for styling from the `unified.css` file.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Do not use deep nesting in CSS.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## JavaScript/TypeScript Rules[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use TypeScript for all logic.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Sections must be auto-instantiated via the `SectionLoader` and `data-section` attributes.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Keep the core bundle small; put page-specific logic in dedicated entry points.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## GitHub Workflow[m
[32m+[m[32m- GitHub Actions is used for CI/CD.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Every push to the main branch is automatically deployed to GitHub Pages.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use Pull Requests for all changes.[m
[32m+[m[32m- PR descriptions should be clear and follow the provided template.[m
